andier provides new insights into Chinese representations of the feminine and the role of women in popular religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aAnthropology -- Asia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aReligion -- Asian. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362057540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503620575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503620575/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles